var. rm(b) ≥ 0, ∀m ∈ M,

(4)

which considers the optimal division of the total bandwidth R of the InP under the GKM. Constraint (2) ensures the isolation between different MVNOs. As the MBS has limited amount of bandwidth, constraint (3) guarantees the allocated bandwidth of all MVNOs not exceed the total bandwidth of the MBS and (4) ensures that the resource allocated to each MVNO must be positive value.
Solving problem (1)-(4) is possible once the valuation of MVNOs is known at the InP. However, the valuation is the private value of each MVNO. Therefore, the MVNOs will not

