where ps is the downlink transmitted power of the BS to a mobile user s. Note that we assume ﬁxed power allocation per
bandwidth (Hertz) in this paper. Moreover, hs is the channel gain of user s, N0 is the noise power, and xm s represents a fraction of bandwidth of MVNO m assigned to s where xm s ∈ rm. (20) and (21) are the constraints for the fraction of wireless bandwidth allocated to each subscriber of the MVNO
m ∈ M. As constraints (20) and (21) are linear, the constraint
set is afﬁne and objective function (19) is concave. Therefore,
the valuation function vm(rm(b)) of each MVNO m ∈ M satisﬁes Assumption 1.

C. Optimal Bandwidth Allocation

The bandwidth allocation problem in (19) is a convex problem. Thus, the optimal solutions for (19) can be obtained via Lagrangian duality [42]. Here, the Lagrangian of (19) is

